Date: 24/7/1975
Source: Otago Daily Times
Author:
Vol / Page: 12
Edition:
Quote: Warning On Thefts From Office Blocks [heading] Office workers in Dunedin have not been plagued by `stair dancers,' but the CIB nevertheless advises people to beware of burglars in office blocks. ... the Wellington police warned office workers to `watch out for stair-dancers.' `Stair-dancing,' an old term used to describe thefts from hotel rooms, is now applied by criminals to the practice of thieving in high-rise office blocks.
Notes:  (Griffiths Collection)

